Eight-hour work days five days in a row really grind me down to the thinnest part of my psyche. My coworker, Jen, sits on that bit of psyche and saws away at it with a bone saw made for a blue whale until it just snaps. And today it snapped.

For reasons beyond me, Jen has a crush on me. Every day at work she will not stop speaking to me, flirting with me.

â€œWhat are you doing today, Aaron?â€

â€œDo you want to hang out tonight, Aaron?â€

â€œI like your shirt today, Aaron.â€

â€œHave you been working out, Aaron?â€

Every time she talks, she ends with this upwards inflection that rings inside me and causes a swift rise of irrational anger. 

Her dull blue eyes look at me with just emptiness behind them, waiting for my response... which is usually just a simple â€œNo.â€ And after months of her no-so-obvious hints, I decided I'd give her what she wants.

I invited her to my home.

â€œHey Jen,â€ I say. 

She quickly turns towards me and smiles, â€œHey Aaron.â€ 

â€œDo you want to hang out at my place tonight?â€

She pauses for a second, not nearly as excited as I expect her to be. After so much prodding, I thought for sure she would lose her mind over the offer. But eventually she responds.

â€œTo do what?â€ She gives me the same empty look she usually does, â€œWell, I mean, of course. I would love to. Are others going to join us?â€

I am perplexed at the question. This is not the response I expected.

â€œI, uh, found this ritual that's supposed to see who your true love is.â€ Iâ€™m making this up on the fly, sheâ€™ll for sure go for it, â€œIt's supposed to work, but I thought you'd like to try it with me.â€ I force a smile.

â€œTrue love?â€ She blinks before offering the strangest smile, â€œYou know what? Sure! Perhaps we will both find out together.â€ She gives a lilting laugh before turning back and returning to work.

â€œUhâ€¦â€ I stand behind her, in a confused haze, â€œRight, well, see you tonight.â€

And with that, I return to work. 
